block.field: A bunch of slash commands; you can see what their function is when you use them.
rp!character [ping an user] --> Makes you see a character from the database.
rp!start --> Creates your character. It's long, though.

shadow.field: Hi. I'll guide you while you create your character. You've got 15 minutes to answer each of the 13 questions.
First of all, say your character's name (just the name, no dots nor other things, and the first letter in capital letters, please):
And how are they called by their friends (Nickname)?:
Ok. When was your character born?
Ok. Let's focus on other things.
And do they have a backstory? If so, send it. And if they don't, write **unknown**, please.
Does your character have a pet? If the answer is yes, describe it. If not, say **unknown**.
What's your character's hometown? If you don't know it, send **unknown**.
That would be all. Thanks for creating your character! Now, each time anyone needs to know something, they can use slash commands to see it.
